  "Tyler earns $4,000/month and spends $600/month on wants: $200 dining out, $120 streaming services, $150 new clothes, and $130 entertainment. If he cuts wants by 30%, how much extra can he save annually?": "",
  "$3,600": "",
  "$2,160": "",
  "$1,080": "",
  "$7,200": "",
  "30% of $600 = $180 per month saved. Annual extra savings = $180 × 12 = $2,160. By cutting wants by less than a third, Tyler finds over $2,000 per year for savings or debt repayment.": "",
  "Emma's friend insists she needs the latest $1,200 smartphone. Emma currently has a fully functional $300 phone. If Emma invests the $900 difference at 8% for 10 years, approximately how much would it grow to?": "",
