  "~$1,943": "",
  "$2,700": "",
  "$900": "",
  "FV = $900 × (1.08)^10 ≈ $1,943. By resisting peer pressure and investing the difference, Emma more than doubles her money in 10 years instead of buying a phone that depreciates immediately.": "",
  "A family earns $6,000/month. Their needs total $3,200, they spend $2,000 on wants, and save $800. A financial advisor recommends the 50/30/20 rule. How should they adjust their wants spending?": "",
