  "A recent graduate earns $40,000/year. She identifies that she spends 40% on needs and 45% on wants, leaving only 15% for savings. To follow the 50/30/20 rule, she needs to redirect how much from wants to savings annually?": "",
  "$2,000": "",
  "$4,000": "",
  "$6,000": "",
  "Current savings = 15% × $40,000 = $6,000. Target = 20% × $40,000 = $8,000. She needs $2,000 more for savings. Current wants = 45% × $40,000 = $18,000; target = 30% × $40,000 = $12,000. Reducing wants by $6,000 covers the $2,000 savings gap plus allows shifting $4,000 to needs if needed.": "",
  "David buys a new $50,000 luxury car instead of a reliable used $20,000 car. If he had invested the $30,000 difference at 7% annual return for 15 years, approximately how much would that investment be worth?": "",
